<p>As a member of the Address Book team I collaborated with other team members and the user 
interface group. Since Mozilla is an ongoing open source project, documentation for API interfaces was sometimes
incomplete.  Working on the Address Book required reading mozilla source code when
documentation was unavailable. It was therefore, on occasion, necessary to read XPCOM C++ code to 
write javascript.  The main elements of programming included XUL, javascript and CSS; the development
operating system was RedHat Linux.
</p>

